<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6973] Trim trailing whitespace from configuration values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6973</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the following properties have a whitespace at the end of the value it causes problems with Kerberos authentication...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hbase.regionserver.keytab.file&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;/etc/hbase/conf/hbase.krb5 &amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;hbase.master.keytab.file&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;value&amp;gt;/etc/hbase/conf/hbase.krb5 &amp;lt;/value&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m guessing this can affect other properties as well, so can the values be trimmed when read?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
